House Resolution 566
By: Representative Reese of the 140th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Congresswoman Lucy McBath; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Congresswoman Lucy McBath has devoted her career to advocating for
3 bipartisan solutions that address gun violence, support small businesses, strengthen the
4 economy, protect veterans, and lower healthcare and prescription drug costs; and
5 WHEREAS, since taking office in January 2019, she has worked across party lines to
6 advance meaningful legislation, earning recognition as an effective lawmaker and a leading
7 voice within the House Democratic Caucus; and
8 WHEREAS, she played a key role in the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, the first
9 comprehensive gun safety legislation in over three decades; championed the HAVEN Act,
10 which provides protections for veterans experiencing financial hardship; and supported a bill
11 to limit the cost of insulin for seniors on Medicare to $35 per month; and
12 WHEREAS, her advocacy in Congress has been shaped by her lived experiences, particularly
13 her unwavering dedication to preventing other families from enduring the pain of losing a
14 loved one to gun violence; and
